description: From Ancient Greek μύσταξ (mústax) +‎ -ial. Compare moustachial.

entries.meaning: Having a fringe of hairs suggestive of a moustache.
Pertaining to the area around the vibrissae on either side of the muzzle of a mammal such as a rodent or cat.
Any of the large rigid whiskers (vibrissae) that appear on the fleshy pads on either side of the muzzle of an animal such as a cat or rodent.
examples: During the third week, the mystacials and ulnarcarpals are the first to form.
